SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1051
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to honor Veterans Month.
WHEREAS, the State of Tennessee is home to more than 440,000 men and women
who have earned the honored title of "veteran"; and
WHEREAS, the State of Tennessee is also home to more than 82,000 veterans who
suffer from service-connected disabilities; and
WHEREAS, veterans from the State of Tennessee have earned thirty-three Medals of
Honor, our nation's highest military honor for heroism in battle; and
WHEREAS, Tennesseans are proud to honor our veterans on November 11 of each
year in accordance with federal law; and
WHEREAS, a single day of special observance is not sufficient to express our
admiration and gratitude to the courageous men and women who have sacrificed greatly in
service to their country; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Veterans Month in November 2026.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
